abstract: Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, said it was “increasingly likely” that more members of his party would push to hear from John R. Bolton about President Trump’s dealings with Ukraine.

headline_main: ‘I’d Like to Hear It,’ Romney Says of Bolton Testimony

abstract: Readers discuss John Bolton’s book, the chief justice’s ability to insist on witnesses, Adam Schiff’s “head on a pike” comment, Lev Parnas and more.

abstract: The new policy revised the so-called public charge rule, making immigrants ineligible for permanent legal status if they use public benefits like Medicaid and food stamps.
snippet: The new policy revised the so-called public charge rule, making immigrants ineligible for permanent legal status if they use public benefits like Medicaid and food stamps.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Monday allowed the Trump administration to move forward with plans to deny green cards to immigrants who are thought to be likely to make even occasional and minor use of public benefits like Medicaid, food stamps and housing vouchers.

abstract: The president plans tariffs on metal items like nails and cables after his earlier move raised the cost of making those products in the United States.
snippet: The president plans tariffs on metal items like nails and cables after his earlier move raised the cost of making those products in the United States.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has announced plans to broaden his tariffs on foreign steel and aluminum, saying the existing tariffs had not proved as effective as he had hoped in reviving American production.

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg is the star of the show at his campaign rallies in Iowa, where his crowds are virtually all white. In South Carolina, in front of black audiences, he still needs help telling his story.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg is the star of the show at his campaign rallies in Iowa, where his crowds are virtually all white. In South Carolina, in front of black audiences, he still needs help telling his story.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES, Iowa — When Pete Buttigieg was asked Thursday if it worried him that mostly white people attended his big rallies in South Carolina, he said yes.

headline_main: Watch Live: Trump Legal Team Resumes Opening Arguments

abstract: Senators hear the second installment of President Trump’s legal defense and arguments for why he should not be removed from office.
snippet: Senators hear the second installment of President Trump’s legal defense and arguments for why he should not be removed from office.
lead_paragraph: President Trump’s lawyers avoided on Monday any mention of a newly disclosed firsthand account from his former national security adviser, John R. Bolton, that directly undercuts one of the defense’s main arguments.

abstract: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
snippet: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
lead_paragraph: Two months ago, Britain’s Prince Andrew issued a public statement saying he would be willing to help American law enforcement officials with their investigation into allegations of sex-trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein and his associates.
